  "response": "Hinduism is a complex religion with many gods and goddesses. Some of the most prominent Hindu deities include:\n\n1. Major Gods:\n- Brahma (Creator)\n- Vishnu (Preserver)\n- Shiva (Destroyer)\n\n2. Important Avatars of Vishnu:\n- Rama\n- Krishna\n- Narasimha\n- Varaha\n- Buddha\n\n3. Powerful Goddesses:\n- Durga\n- Kali\n- Lakshmi\n- Saraswati\n- Parvati\n\n4. Other Significant Deities:\n- Ganesha (God of wisdom)\n- Hanuman (Monkey God)\n- Kartikeya (God of war)\n- Indra (King of gods)\n- Surya (Sun God)\n\n5. Regional Deities:\n- Jagannath\n- Ayyappa\n- Murugan\n\nThese gods represent different aspects of divine energy, cosmic principles, and natural forces. Hindus believe in one supreme divine power (Brahman) manifested through multiple deities. Each god has unique characteristics, symbolism, and spiritual significance.\n\nThe number of Hindu gods is vast, with some traditions suggesting 330 million different divine forms.",
